      "settings": {
        "label": "Types of Peptides",
        "headline": "Understanding Peptide Categories",
        "body": "<p><strong>Signal Peptides</strong> communicate with fibroblast cells, encouraging them to support collagen production. These peptides help maintain skin firmness and resilience over time.</p><p><strong>Carrier Peptides</strong> help transport trace minerals that support enzymatic processes within the skin.</p><p><strong>Neurotransmitter Peptides</strong> are designed to influence the interaction between nerves and muscles in the skin, helping soften the appearance of expression lines.</p>",
